author: @breadstickcrumb
text: Sometimes people talk about how this choreo isn’t as in sync as svt’s other dances, but I think as a dancer and choreographer, each person will differ in what they focus on. Dino, while also focusing on the base choreography, tends to put more energy and focus towards emotions and passions of each dancer and the overall feeling (big picture) rather than the synchronization of each dancer themselves. But that’s just my take I guess. Just because a dance isn’t as in sync in terms of having the exact same path they take and the same degree that their hand is extended in, doesn’t mean it’s bad and not in sync. The important parts that Dino wants to highlight are still emphasized in the choreography. I think it’s quite refreshing to see everyone dancing more distinctly in their own style. They all really shine c:

Pledis may begin posting videos of ALL their artists on the Pledis Entertainment channel, including their MVs. Unsubscribing to that channel (if you were in the first place) or trending on Twitter that you don’t agree with the decision probably won’t do anything. Getting Pledis to start posting on the individual artists’ channels again is not worth potentially sabotaging the groups’ success by refusing to stream or share on other platforms. MV views make up a sizeable percentage of the criteria to win on a lot of music shows, as most of us are aware, and it’s one of the most direct ways for us to support them. We can’t really do anything as fans; we hold little to no authority over this matter.

The teaser for the Getting Closer MV has already been posted there.

author: @leadercoups736
text:
WHO’S WHO - For all you new/baby carats! These are in order of their parts btw~ Welcome to the diamond life ^^

- White shirt and open grey button up - Jeonghan (Vocal Unit)

- Blond hair w/ black and white striped shirt- Seungkwan (Vocal Unit)

- Red Balenciaga shirt and bucket hat- Minghao/The8 (Performance Unit)

- White shirt and open blue color-blocked jacket- Wonwoo (Hip Hop Unit)

author: @citraseptiadewi887
text:
솔직히 나는 자랑 스럽습니다 carat 나는 17 살이 정말 좋아요. 나는 항상 언제 어디서나 17을 지원하고 동반 할 수 있기를 바랍니다.
17 명의 회원 중에서 누가 가장 재능이 있고 가장 중요한 사람인지는 바보 같은 문제입니다. 17 세는 서로 보완적인 보이스 밴드 그룹입니다. 당신의 꿈을 향해 계속 도전해라 carat 항상 당신을지지한다.
나는 정말로 당신의 투쟁마다 동행하고 싶습니다. 그러나 나는 멀리서 당신을 위해서만기도 할 수 있습니다 :)
Translate:
honestly, I'm proud to be carat I really like seventeen. I hope that I can always support and accompany seventeen wherever and whenever.
if it's about who is the most talented or most important among seventeen members, that's a stupid problem. seventeen is a boy band group whose members complement each other. keep on reaching for your dreams, carat always support you
I really want to accompany each of your struggles. but I can only pray for you from afar :)

author: @sissymayemaye
text:
To Pledis Entertainment:
For those of us who are relatively new Carats, THANK YOU!!!!! 
I only became a fan last year (I mistakenly thought the boys were under SM who I was personally protesting the treatment of their artists at the time), and therefore had to take a SEVENTEEN crash course to catch up with all the other Carats and make up for lost time, lol ! As I got to know SEVENTEEN, there were two songs that stood out and completely defined them to me. The first was Smile Flowers, which moved me SO much, it inspired me to write my first chapter fanfic (Soonhoon/HoWoo centric--I'll put the link below in case you care to inspect, lol), and THIS song, Flower. This song inspired me to pull out my old chain belts and ankle bells and start bellydancing again. So naturally, when I saw this notification, I immediately clicked, and I was NOT disappointed!! I LOVE IT!! My heart will always belong to Hoshi, but Dino got to shine in this one, and I'm sure his big brother was in the wings cheering for him along with everyone else ( or should I say his twin. As much as the two of them protest, they DO look alike. When they have similar hair color, I've gotten them confused several times, lol)!!
Anyway, thanks again, Pledis for giving us such wonderful talented boys and for taking good care of their health and for letting them do awesome side projects such as these that showcase their talent! Kamsahamnida!!
(https://www.asianfanfics.com/story/view/1339982/smile-flower-fanfic-hospital-hurt-sick-faint-seventeen-injured-woozi-hoshi-bleeding-unconscious-ambulance)
